    },
    "default_locale": "en-US",
    "description": {
        "en-US": "As of version 2.0.0.0, Thunderbird still forces you to go through an awkward process of opening a properties window if you want to be able to check a folder for new items. If you have a large number of folders, this quickly becomes very annoying. FolderCheck adds a new item to the context menu for folders that allows you to quickly and easily toggle the \"check this folder for new messages\" setting.\n\nUpdate: I will be adding a better interface in the near future to allow you to mass-select folders to be checked. If possible, I also plan to make \"check for new messages\" the default for new folders."
    },
